{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-00145/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-00145"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:01:45"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tilt"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["high key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man sits on a wooden stool and pulls a sock up to his knee."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-00145","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-00145"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1/e0b1feac-af67-48e9-85a8-ff59fe446045","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:04:43.500Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds occupies the left side of the frame rather than the center as he puts on his socks, an indication that something within him is slightly askew.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:274.4671532846715,19.521897810219038,540.1204379562046,946.521897810219"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1/29a2e39f-097a-46b4-a190-07b7c0074902","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:05:19.884Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW250189607 BCX0\" href=\"https://deadline.com/2018/01/phantom-thread-mark-bridges-daniel-day-lewis-costumes-interview-1202226303/\"><u>In an interview with Deadline,</u></a> costume designer Mark Bridges called these socks “Pope socks” as he revealed that they are a product of Sartoria Gammarelli in Rome. Gammarelli has been crafting and tailoring papal (and ecclesiastic) clothing&nbsp; since 1798. The purple socks that Reynolds wears are in fact associated with bishops; the Pope wears white Gammarelli socks.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:848.0255474452555,148.478102189781,806.978102189781,858.8430656934306"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1/d54e951a-26df-447f-92b5-163cd85cae5c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:05:40.785Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Reynolds completes his morning routine, we start to get a sense of his commitment to discipline and regimentation, which we can glean through the blocking.&nbsp; As he polishes his shoes, puts on his socks, and dresses himself, we see him placed within the boundaries of a doorway. This placement conveys Reynold’s methodical lifestyle. While Reynolds is placed within the boundary of a doorway, the door remains open. While Reynolds is satisfied acting out this ritualistic performance he’s created for himself, the open door implies an ability to change, when the right person walks in.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-00145/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:18.613138686131414,38.813868613138744,210.74452554744522,168.7226277372263"}}}]}]}]}